description:
Responsibilities:

Perform reception duties including telephone calls, greeting and serving visitors in professional manner;
Provide general office administrative work and clerical supports;
Support ad-hoc assignments.

Requirements: 

Diploma in Hospitality or related disciplines preferred;
1 year's working experience in service field preferred, fresh graduate will also be considered;
Strong sense of responsibility, proactive, energetic, pleasant and customer-oriented;
Good PC knowledge in MS Office & Chinese Word Processing;
Proficiency in both written & spoken English and Chinese including Mandarin;
Immediate available is preferred.

Working Location: Hong Kong Science Park, Tai Po

We offer 5-day working week and an attractive remuneration package. Interest parties please click Apply Now. For company details, please visit www.purapharm.com.

Our Company is an equal opportunity employer. All personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only, while the personal data of the unsuccessful applicants will be destroyed within 6 months after the recruitment process.

The appointee is expected to carry out general administrative duties for Division of Continuing and Professional Education. Major duties include: (a) assisting in the day-to-day operation of the programmes, including but not limited to class scheduling, examination arrangement, student record updating, and organisation of student activities; (b) liaising with internal and external parties (including staff, students and external bodies) and handling enquiries and complaints; (c) compiling information and figures and maintaining database / file records; and (d) providing supports to ad-hoc duties as assigned by the supervisor(s).
Minimum Requirements:
 (i) Holder of Higher Diploma or Associate Degree with preferably 2 years of related experience; OR (ii) with at least 5 passes in HKCEE including English Language (at least Grade C if Syllabus A/Level 2 from 2007) and Chinese Language (at least Level 2 from 2007), or at least 5 subjects attaining Level 2 in HKDSE including English Language and Chinese Language with more work experience;
Holder of Bachelor’s degree with at least 1 year of work experience will also be considered;
Effective interpersonal and multi-tasking skills;
Able to work under tight schedule;
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese; and
Proficient in MS Office applications (English and Chinese) and Excel.
Salary will be commensurate with qualifications and experience.
Application Procedure:
Applicants are invited to submit their applications at the HKBU e-Recruitment System (jobs.hkbu.edu.hk). Shortlisted candidates will be invited to sit for written test. Applicants not invited for interview 8 weeks after the closing date may consider their applications unsuccessful. Details of the University's Personal Information Collection Statement can be found at http://hro.hkbu.edu.hk/pics.
The School reserves the right not to make an appointment for the post advertised, and the appointment will be made according to the terms and conditions then applicable at the time of offer.
Closing date: 31 January 2022

Main Duties:

  Perform all-round reception counter service, answer phone calls and general enquiries;
  Record and distribute incoming and outgoing mails/couriers and e-Fax etc.;
  Handle meeting room bookings and provide logistic support for Council / Committee meetings;
  Record and ensure office stationery supplies and distribution;
  Responsible for record grant applications registrations and distribution;
  Provide departmental administrative and clerical support;
  Other ad-hoc duties assigned by supervisors

Requirements:

  F.5 graduate with 5 passes in HKDSE or above; minimum 1-year working experience;
  Pleasant, courteous with good telephone manner and good communication skills in both English and Chinese;
  Proficient in MS Office and Chinese word processing;
  Punctual, work independently and good at multi-tasking;
  Able to work on Saturday/Sunday occasionally;
  Fresh graduates with some working experience may also be considered.

Salary offered will be commensurate with qualifications and experience. Interested parties, please send CV with details on education and work experience, stating salary history and expected salary, and indicating your earliest availability to the Human Resources Department, 10/F, 1063 King’s Road, Quarry Bay, Hong Kong no later than 4 February 2022. Please quote the job reference on the envelope.

Applicants not invited for interview within 16 weeks from the closing date for application may assume that their applications are unsuccessful. Personal data collected will be treated in strictest confidence and will only be used for recruitment purposes. HKADC reserves the right to consider late applications and not to make appointment for the post advertised. We do not accept applications through e-mail or fax.

HKADC is an Equal Opportunities Employer

