Job Description:

Perform reception duties and office admin;
Handle incoming call, room booking and great client;
Outdoor work and other ad hoc duties may be required;

Attractive salary with medical benefits and provident fund provided. For interested candidates, please contact Grandall Zimmern Law Firm. – Attn. : HR Department at 14/F., The Hong Kong Club Building, 3A Chater Road, Central, Hong Kong

The appointee will be assigned to the Learning Centre Administration Section of the School to provide administrative and clerical support in the day-to-day operation. Duties include but not limited to: a) assisting in daily class operation and teaching equipment / centre facilities preparation; b) maintaining records, preparing reports, and performing administrative duties such as filing and photocopying; c) data inputting and compiling; d) providing frontline support for classes and counter services including enquiry handling; and e) coordinating and liaising with internal and external parties such as instructors, students and contractors. The appointee is also required to perform shift duty on weekday evenings.
Minimum Requirements:
HKCEE 5 passes including English Language (at least grade C if Syllabus A / Level 2 from 2007), or at least 5 subjects attaining Level 2 in HKDSE including English Language and Chinese Language, or Yi Jin graduates;
At least 2 years of relevant experience;
Good communication and customer services skills;
Competency in computer software applications;
Knowledge in basic operation and setup of audio-visual equipment is an advantage; and
Holders of Associate Degree / Higher Diploma with less experience may also be considered.
Salary will be commensurate with qualifications and experience.
Application Procedure:
Applicants are invited to submit their applications at the HKBU e-Recruitment System (jobs.hkbu.edu.hk). Applicants not invited for interview 8 weeks after the closing date may consider their applications unsuccessful. Details of the University's Personal Information Collection Statement can be found at http://hro.hkbu.edu.hk/pics.
The School reserves the right not to make an appointment for the post advertised, and the appointment will be made according to the terms and conditions then applicable at the time of offer.
Closing date: 24 January 2022

Responsibilities:

Perform receptionist functions including but not limited to greeting and serving tea to guests, handling phone calls,mailing courier;

Handle day to day office administration duties including procurement of office stationery and equipment maintenanceand ensure all records are up to date;

Ensure smooth operation of the reception counter to co-ordinate all in/out mails/parcels with couriers or internal office assistants, handle simple outdoor works when required;

Other ad hoc duties as assigned.

Requirements:

F.5/DSE or above;

Relevant experience in Receptionist and administration preferred;
Strong communication skills;

Mature, independent, detail minded with strong sense of responsibility;

Good command of both written and spoken Cantonese, Mandarin and English;

Proficient in MS Office (Word, Excel) and Chinese input is must.

Responsibilities:

To perform full spectrum of office administration functions, include but not limited to procurement of office equipment & maintenance, stationary, pantry and utility items.
Perform general clerical duties to include but not limited to incoming calls, mails handling, greeting visitors, maintaining meeting rooms schedule, filing and other administrative supports;
Assist to setup and coordinate meetings and conferences;
Sourcing, purchasing and recording all company materials and inventory control, e.g. stationery, sundries items;
Coordinate conference room bookings;
Assist to coordinate Company events, such as Christmas Party, Annual Dinner etc;
Organize all office helper’s working schedule and monitor their working performance, to ensure the office environment in tidy up, clean and comfortable conditions;
Handling other administrative duties as required;
Other duties as assigned by supervisor.

Requirements:



Higher Diploma in Business related disciplines
With 1-3 years or above experience in Administration field
Attention to detail and problem-solving skills;
Good command of written and spoken in English and Chinese; Fluency in Putonghua is an advantage
Strong organizational skills with the ability to multi-task;
Proficiency in MS Office, and Chinese word processing ;
Ability to work independently and willingness to take up responsibility ;

We offer competitive package to right candidate, including but unlimited double pay, performance bonus, free lunch, shuttle bus, education allowance, housing allowance, Medical and other benefits.

Working hours : Monday to Friday 9:00am to 5:00pm & Saturday 9:00am to 12:00noon

Interested parties please send full resume in Chinese and English in strict confidence with expected salary & earliest availability to us for interview.

For more details, please visit www.tienchu.com

